EmailTemplate.subject: Kindergarten Open Morning: Wednesday 31 August
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Dear {!Contact.FirstName}
I'd like to invite you and the families of {!Account.Name} along to our upcoming Kindergarten Open Morning. It's a wonderful opportunity for preschool families to visit our vibrant Junior School.
During their visit families will see the Kinder class at work, meet our Junior School staff and hear first hand about the engaging Kindergarten and Junior School programs offered at St Andrew's Cathedral School. Further details attached.
Bookings are essential. Please book your place via our website at http://www.sacs.nsw.edu.au/events/kindyopenmorning2015
I look forward to welcoming you on the day.
Regards
Bruce Perry
Registrar
_______________________________________________________
Kindergarten Open Morning
High academic culture - Coeducation - Every child matters
Discover the benefits of Kindergarten at St Andrew's where children are provided with an exceptional start to their school education.
Wednesday 9 September
9:00am to 10.30am
SACS Library Auditorium,
St Andrew's House, Sydney Square, Sydney
Bookings: http://www.sacs.nsw.edu.au/contentpages/Book-a-Kindergarten-Tour
Event programme:
Parents will hear from the Head of School and Head of Junior School about some of the many benefits of an education at St Andrew’s, while pre-schoolers will be invited to experience "big school". Children will enjoy several exciting and entertaining classroom activities conducted by current Kindergarten teachers before being escorted to the rooftop playground for morning tea.
In the unique environment at St Andrew's, your child will be a vital part of a happy, vibrant school. We offer:
Small class sizes; Accelerated classes; A strong focus on numeracy and literacy; Memory skills training for every student; Specialist teachers in sport, music, drama, language; Extensive cocurricular activities available from Kindergarten; Accessible after school and vacation care; Authentic Christian values.
This is a wonderful opportunity for your pre-schooler to visit "big school" (and even make some friends before they start!).
St Andrew's is a place where students are encouraged to have hearts that love, minds that grow and lives that give
Bruce Perry Registrar/Mathematics Teacher
